2026-03-19 00:52:47 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Philip Morris International Inc earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'response_time': 1.73, 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/future', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Future Growth', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$295.5b\n\n# Philip Morris International Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\nPhilip Morris International is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 8.4% and 6.4% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 8.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 1315.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n8.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n8.66%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco earnings growth | 7.6% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.4% |\n| Future return on equity | 1,315.67% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 19 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026 [...] ## Analyst Future Growth Forecasts\n\nEarnings vs Savings Rate: PM's forecast earnings growth (8.4% per year) is above the savings rate (3.4%).\n\nEarnings vs Market: PM's earnings (8.4% per year) are forecast to grow slower than the US market (15.6% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Earnings: PM's earnings are forecast to grow, but not significantly.\n\nRevenue vs Market: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than the US market (10.3% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Revenue: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than 20% per year.\n\n## Earnings per Share Growth Forecasts\n\n## Future Return on Equity\n\nFuture ROE: PM's Return on Equity is forecast to be very high in 3 years time (1315.7%).\n\n## Discover growth companies\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y [...] ### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next\n\n## Recent updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Group CEO & Director recently sold US$15m worth of stock\n\n### Group CEO & Director notifies of intention to sell stock\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026", 'score': 0.9379027, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.morningstar.com/news/dow-jones/202602064776/philip-morris-posts-higher-4q-profit-revenue-forecasts-continued-growth', 'title': 'Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts ...', 'content': "Morningstar\n\n# Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued Growth\n\nBy Connor Hart\n\nPhilip Morris International logged higher profit and revenue in the fourth quarter, while forecasting continued growth for years to come.\n\nThe tobacco company--which sells cigarettes such as Marlboro and Parliament in overseas markets, as well as smokeless tobacco such as Zyn worldwide--posted operating income of $3.4 billion, up 3.5% from a year earlier. Earnings came in at $1.37 a share.\n\nStripping out certain one-time items, earnings were $1.70 a share. That was in line with analysts' expectations for adjusted earnings, according to FactSet.\n\nRevenue increased 6.8% to $10.36 billion, just below Wall Street views for $10.38 billion. [...] Total shipment volumes edged 0.1% higher to 193.8 billion units.\n\nChief Executive Jacek Olczak said 2025 marked the company's fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with results boosted by continued growth across its smoke-free business and operating margin expansion.\n\nFor the current quarter, the company expects adjusted earnings of $1.80 to $1.85 a share, compared with analyst views for $1.89 a share.\n\nLooking ahead, Philip Morris guided for earnings of $7.87 to $8.02 a share in 2026. On an adjusted basis, earnings are projected to come in between $8.38 and $8.53 a share. Analysts were looking for earnings of $8.01 a share, or $8.34 a share on an adjusted basis.\n\nThe forecast assumes net revenue growth of 5% to 7% for the year, as well as organic operating income growth of 7$ to 9%. [...] The company additionally disclosed its compounded annual growth targets through 2028, calling for a 6% to 8% increase for net revenues, an 8% to 10% increase for operating income, and a 9% to 11% increase for adjusted per-share earnings.\n\nWrite to Connor Hart at connor.hart@wsj.com\n\n(END) Dow Jones Newswires\n\nFebruary 06, 2026 07:53 ET (12:53 GMT)\n\nThe articles, information, and content displayed on this webpage may\ninclude materials prepared and provided by third parties. Such\nthird-party content is offered for informational purposes only and\nis not endorsed, reviewed, or verified by Morningstar.", 'score': 0.93338853, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tradingview.com/news/tradingview:168c3bfea5aba:0-philip-morris-international-reports-2025-fourth-quarter-full-year-results/', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & ...', 'content': "Future Outlook\n\nPMI provided a full-year 2026 forecast with reported diluted EPS expected to be in the range of $7.87 to $8.02. The company also set compound annual growth targets for 2026-2028, aiming for 6% to 8% net revenue growth, 8% to 10% operating income growth, and 9% to 11% adjusted diluted EPS growth, excluding currency impacts.\n\nOriginal SEC Filing: [Philip Morris International Inc. [ PM ] - 8-K - Feb. 06, 2026](\n\n## PM chart\n\n## Latest news\n\n## More news from TradingView [...] TradingView\nTradingView\n\n# Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year Results\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. (PMI) has released its financial results for the fourth quarter and full year of 2025. The company reported significant growth in its smoke-free product (SFP) segment, contributing to overall revenue and profit increases. The report also includes forward-looking statements and growth targets for the upcoming years.\n\nFinancial Highlights [...] Financial Highlights\n\nFor the full year 2025, PMI reported a diluted EPS of $7.26, a substantial increase from $4.52 in 2024. The adjusted diluted EPS was $7.54, representing a growth of 14.8%, and 14.2% on a currency-neutral basis. Net revenues surpassed $40 billion, with the smoke-free business contributing close to $17 billion. The company's gross profit increased by 11.1% to $27.3 billion.\n\nBusiness and Operational Highlights", 'score': 0.89053273, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/philip-morris-international-earnings-report-highlights', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Inc. (NYSE:PM) Earning... | FMP', 'content': "Despite the revenue miss, Philip Morris reported an increase in both profit and revenue for the fourth quarter. The company remains optimistic about its future, forecasting continued growth. This optimism is supported by PMI's fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with net revenues surpassing $40 billion in 2025. Notably, nearly $17 billion of this revenue came from its smoke-free business.\n\nThe company's stock price has experienced a decline, attributed to the softer-than-expected revenue figures. This has put pressure on PM's shares, causing a decrease in their value, as noted by Barrons. Despite this, PMI's strong performance in recent years, including significant operating margin expansion, highlights its resilience and strategic success. [...] # Philip Morris International Inc. (NYSE:PM) Earnings Report Highlights\n\nBy Tony Dante\n\nFeb 06, 2026\n\nGet More PMData\n\nFMP API\n\nCompany ProfileFinancial StatementsAnalyst EstimatesDividends\n\n Philip Morris International Inc. (NYSE:PM) reported an EPS of $1.70, matching estimates, but revenue of $10.36 billion slightly missed expectations.\n The company has seen its fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with net revenues surpassing $40 billion in 2025, nearly $17 billion of which came from its smoke-free business.\n Despite a decline in stock price due to softer-than-expected revenue figures, PMI's strong performance and strategic focus on smoke-free products position it well for future success. [...] Philip Morris International Inc. (NYSE:PM) is a leading tobacco company known for its popular cigarette brands and Zyn nicotine pouches. On February 6, 2026, PM reported its earnings, revealing an earnings per share (EPS) of $1.70, which matched the estimated EPS. However, the company's revenue of $10.36 billion slightly missed the expected $10.40 billion, as highlighted by the Wall Street Journal.", 'score': 0.8875269, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pmi.com/media-center/press-releases/press-details/?newsId=29646', 'title': 'Reaffirms 2026 Full-Year Forecast', 'content': 'The presentation will cover:\n\n2026 Full-Year Forecast\n\nPMI reaffirms its 2026 full-year reported diluted EPS forecast, announced on February 6th, of $7.87 to $8.02. Excluding a total 2026 adjustment of $0.51 per share, the forecast range for adjusted diluted EPS of $8.38 - $8.53 represents a projected increase of 11.1% to 13.1% versus $7.54 in 2025. Excluding a favorable currency impact, at then prevailing exchange rates, of $0.27 per share, this represents growth of 7.5% to 9.5%, as shown below.\n\nThe assumptions underlying this forecast remain unchanged versus those communicated by PMI in its earnings release of February 6, 2026.\n\nFactors described in the Forward-Looking and Cautionary Statements section of this release represent continuing risks to these projections.', 'score': 0.8719229, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tikr.com/blog/with-25-returns-last-year-can-philip-morris-stock-keep-rising-in-2026', 'title': 'With 25% Returns Last Year, Can Philip Morris Stock Keep ...', 'content': 'Last updated Feb 7, 2026\n\n### Key Takeaways:\n\n Profit Outlook Reset: Philip Morris raised 2026 EPS growth to 11% to 13% as smoke-free products exceeded 40% of revenue, reinforcing Philip Morris International’s shift away from combustible volume dependence.\n Category Pressure Signals: Philip Morris flagged rising competition in U.S. nicotine pouches as ZYN volumes rose 19% while revenue declined.\n Valuation Anchor: Based on 7% revenue growth, 41% operating margins, and a 20x exit multiple, Philip Morris International stock could reach $220 by December 2028.\n Return Math: From the current price of $183, Philip Morris International implies 20% total upside over 3 years, translating to a 7% annualized return under conservative valuation assumptions.', 'score': 0.8412138, 'raw_content': None}], 'request_id': 'b655f305-dfca-4bf0-b114-3dab11f36f3f'}
